modules.description: This module enables declarative DOM construction and reactive programming through the `Lwd.t` type, offering element creators for HTML5 tags like `div`, `button`, and `input` that support attributes, event handlers, and dynamic children. It distinguishes between content-bearing elements (`cons`) and void elements (`void_cons`), ensuring type-safe manipulation of block, inline, and self-closing tags. It is particularly suited for building dynamic web interfaces where UI components update reactively to data changes while maintaining semantic HTML structure.

This module provides functions for constructing and manipulating HTML elements declaratively, using the `Lwd.t` type to enable reactive updates. It includes element creators for HTML5 tags such as `div`, `button`, and `input`, supporting dynamic attributes, event handlers, and children. Use it to build interactive web interfaces where components automatically update in response to data changes, ensuring correct HTML structure and separation between content and void elements.
